rComments: Critiques unhelpful, completely different evaluations with grade vs. critique. Very incredibly subjective course, either likes your work or not, important to make a good first impression to positively affect your grade? Not ideal.

She is an amazing prof and very honest in her evaluations. If she likes it or doesn't like it she has a reason and every time I've examined and utilized her critique my art has improved. Not for the weak of heart but if you truly want to improve as an artist she's a must!

Very unclear, though quick to criticize on what she does NOT like without explaining properly what she WOULD like to see. Made a girl cry. Unintentionally mean, but not sadistic. Causes students to be continually frustrated. Nice to talk to after class, nice lady, not a terrific teacher.

A mousy, insignificant presence who merely sits back and judges without giving any imput into her arbitrary student assignments.  Very cold, a terrible instructor, and just plain unpleasant.  Never releases her evaluations to the anti-calendar, if that says anything about her comfort as a professor.
Although I expected more feedback in class from projects, If you actually take the time to talk to her after class she is very helpfull.  Also a great artist!  Great Prof. to have!
